cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks such as object segmentation and video segmentation, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper utilizes natural language processing techniques such as word embeddings, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel multi-modal interaction module, which involves learning from both visual and semantic inputs, indicating that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of few-shot learning techniques further suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel setup for video segmentation, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
